result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and PAC Cause Injury (2+). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, PAC Cause Injury (2+) was dismissed by the court.

  • Kimberly S. Artac was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Deft pleads guilty to count 3; found guilty by the Court.  Sentencing arguments.  Deft fined $1200 plus costs.  Bond to apply.  Balance due in 30 days.  IN default, 29 days work crew or 58 days KCJ consec.  Deft sentenced to 360 days.  To commence forthwith.  Credit for 6 days.  Huber for work, medical appts, & treatment.  All non-working hours are to be spent in the KCJ.  DL revoked for 36mos.  Ignition interlock ordered for 36 mos.  Remaining counts are dismissed on State's motion.
